{"type":"message","id":"5d9cea05","parentId":"1afcb076","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:53:26.964Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse script is still running. Let me poll it and also read the most recent log file.","thinkingSignature":"e7d4cd00cd1168e368edfcfb9e0615836b6ade272dd1c61e955dcde71d846ece"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3p5kfqau4dhm_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"tide-reef","timeout":90000}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3p5kfqau4dhm_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 005115.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":402,"output":118,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12474,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774328003815}}
{"type":"message","id":"e2d17812","parentId":"5d9cea05","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:54:21.945Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3p5kfqau4dhm_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5245\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2812\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] tic/tic_classifier.py\r\n[mutation proposed] tic/tic_classifier.py\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 005314 - The TIC experiment requires a working classifier. The pulse logs exist but no implementation tool is present to analyze them for invariants. A Python classifier script is the most direct way to begin testing the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tide-reef","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5245\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2812\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] tic/tic_classifier.py\r\n[mutation proposed] tic/tic_classifier.py\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 005314 - The TIC experiment requires a working classifier. The pulse logs exist but no implementation tool is present to analyze them for invariants. A Python classifier script is the most direct way to begin testing the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774328061943}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c1e4cdd","parentId":"e2d17812","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:54:21.960Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3p5kfqau4dhm_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 005115\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. Key insight: Compression-Causal Duality has been identified\r\n3. Next action: TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n4. Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe pending action is clear: Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\nI should create a script or module that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs (last 20)\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant or variant\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Measures accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the logs directory to understand the structure of pulse logs.\r\n\r\nSince this is a stateless discontinuous agent, I need to be specific about a concrete action. The most immediate next step for the TIC experiment would be to create the TIC classifier implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that will:\r\n1. Load recent pulse logs\r\n2. Implement the invariant/variant classification\r\n3. Run the experiment\r\n4. Output results\r\n\r\nI'll write a `tic_experiment.py` script.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can distinguish invariant (causal) vs variant content across pulse logs, then measure prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment script that loads pulse logs, classifies invariant vs variant content, measures classification accuracy, and attempts next-pulse prediction. This directly addresses the pending \"Implement TIC classifier\" task.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load last n pulse logs sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = []\r\n    for f in sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:n]:\r\n        logs.append(f.read_text())\r\n    return list(reversed(logs))  # Chronological order\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_blocks(log_text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract major content blocks from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    blocks = []\r\n    # Extract sections: OBSERVATION, ACTION, MUTATION, thinking\r\n    sections = re.split(r\"\\n(?=### )\", log_text)\r\n    for s in sections:\r\n        s = s.strip()\r\n        if s and len(s) > 20:\r\n            blocks.append(s)\r\n    return blocks\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariant_score(block, all_blocks):\r\n    \"\"\"Score how 'invariant' a block is across all pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    # Invariant = appears repeatedly with similar structure\r\n    # Variant = unique or rapidly changing\r\n    \r\n    # Simple heuristic: word overlap with other blocks\r\n    words = set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', block.lower()))\r\n    if not words:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    overlaps = []\r\n    for other in all_blocks:\r\n        if other == block:\r\n            continue\r\n        other_words = set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', other.lower()))\r\n        if other_words:\r\n            overlap = len(words & other_words) / len(words)\r\n            overlaps.append(overlap)\r\n    \r\n    if overlaps:\r\n        return sum(overlaps) / len(overlaps)\r\n    return 0.0\r\n\r\ndef classify_blocks(logs):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify blocks as invariant (>0.4 score) or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    all_blocks = []\r\n    for log in logs:\r\n        all_blocks.extend(extract_content_blocks(log))\r\n    \r\n    # Deduplicate\r\n    all_blocks = list(dict.fromkeys(all_blocks))\r\n    \r\n    results = []\r\n    for block in all_blocks:\r\n        score = compute_invariant_score(block, all_blocks)\r\n        classification = \"INVARIANT\" if score > 0.4 else \"VARIANT\"\r\n        results.append((block[:100], score, classification))\r\n    \r\n    return results, all_blocks\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariant_blocks, target_log):\r\n    \"\"\"Attempt to predict content of target pulse from invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    target_blocks = extract_content_blocks(target_log)\r\n    predicted = []\r\n    \r\n    for inv_block in invariant_blocks:\r\n        # Check if invariant patterns appear in target\r\n        inv_words = set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', inv_block.lower()))\r\n        for t_block in target_blocks:\r\n            t_words = set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', t_block.lower()))\r\n            if inv_words and t_words:\r\n                overlap = len(inv_words & t_words) / len(inv_words)\r\n                if overlap > 0.3:\r\n                    predicted.append(inv_block[:50])\r\n                    break\r\n    \r\n    return predicted\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC experiment and report results.\"\"\"\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    print(\"TIC EXPERIMENT - Temporal Invariance Compression\")\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    \r\n    logs = load_pulse_logs(20)\r\n    print(f\"\\nLoaded {len(logs)} pulse logs\")\r\n    \r\n    if len(logs) < 5:\r\n        print(\"ERROR: Need at least 5 logs for meaningful experiment\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    #\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:51:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774328061945}}
